wSUh_wGQV58xjRuedng==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test file structure**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to use one test file for the active class. I could leave a placeholder, but it’s not dedicated and might not cause issues. I’m thinking about changing it to a lightweight test or removing the placeholder entirely. The existing placeholder seems to be scaffold-only, which might not be what’s required. I wonder if it’s better to leave it as it is. Also, I need to ensure the package isn’t a library and determine the class operations properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jO27atYCm27Sqfxs74XJw8f6|fc_0ea79749bdc4942b0169ff785b6ccc8193ad53b9d7989272e8", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.specs2/specs2-common_3/4.20.5/main/extracted/org/specs2/reflect/ClassName.scala", "offset": 1, "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1853, "output": 963, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23296, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778350155701, "responseId": "resp_0ea79749bdc4942b0169ff784c39a481939c5aa742e56cd911"}}
